    {
      "id": "be0280622db3706703af8af3a6fa9d993c679784",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-01-30 08:29:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nI have no fundamental objection to this patch landing, though my inspection is by no means comprehensive as I am not familiar with the MD RAID code myself.\n\nBeyond the one bug pointed out inline that blocks this patch from landing, some things to point out:\n- we are trying to get to a patchless server kernel, and adding more patches will not improve things\n- having clear descriptions at the beginning of each patch makes it much easier to understand (e.g. bh_lru_size_config.patch)\n- it makes sense to try and submit these patches to the upstream kernel so that they don't need to keep being updated\n\nI don't think these issues should prevent the patches from landing, but this is something to address for the next release.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 6
    },
