    {
      "id": "545d6b525a604de3ff013b409d04620e586d2e89",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-05-17 23:32:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 8:\n\nDenis,\nmy comments and questions in the previous two inspections were not addressed (e.g. descriptive comments for each of the patches, performance tests, plans for upstream submission).\n\nIs there any plan for Xyratex to submit these patches to the upstream MD RAID maintainer?  We are trying to remove all Lustre patches to the core kernel, so that users can install Lustre against a vendor kernel, and these ones are a big step in the opposite direction.  Another option would be to create a separate MD RAID module with these patches, so that it can be installed with an unpatched vendor kernel instead of having to patch the kernel itself.\n\nDo you have any benchmarks which show the improvement that is gained from these patches against the mainline MD RAID code?  That would be necessary for upstream submission as well, so it is time well spent.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 8
    },
    {
      "id": "df4e6f724ede49afc7c62d3a65751252d789ba44",
